  "chapter": {
    "number": 2,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Teaching Sound Doctrine"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "But as for you, speak the things that are consistent with sound doctrine."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "Older men are to be temperate, dignified, self-controlled, and sound in faith, love, and perseverance."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          "Older women, likewise, are to be reverent in their behavior, not slanderers or addicted to much wine, but teachers of good."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          "In this way they can train the young women to love their husbands and children,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          "to be self-controlled, pure, managers of their households, kind, and submissive to their own husbands, so that the word of God will not be discredited."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          "In the same way, urge the younger men to be self-controlled."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          "In everything, show yourself to be an example by doing good works. In your teaching show integrity, dignity,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          "and wholesome speech that is above reproach, so that anyone who opposes us will be ashamed to have nothing bad to say about us."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "Slaves are to submit to their own masters in everything, to be well-pleasing, not argumentative,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "not stealing from them, but showing all good faith, so that in every respect they will adorn the teaching about God our Savior."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Godâ€™s Grace Brings Salvation"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "For the grace of God has appeared, bringing salvation to everyone."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          "It instructs us to renounce ungodliness and worldly passions, and to live sensible, upright, and godly lives in the present age,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          "as we await the blessed hope and glorious appearance of our great God and Savior Jesus Christ."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "He gave Himself for us to redeem us from all lawlessness and to purify for Himself a people for His own possession, zealous for good deeds."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "Speak these things as you encourage and rebuke with all authority. Let no one despise you."
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": []
  },
